        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">REVISION DESCRIPTION</emph>
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Added second note regarding engines affected</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Updated parts table to clarify part usage</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>International Truck and Engine Corporation has determined that MaxxForce DT, 9 and 10 engines
                    could experience a water pump pulley separation. Paint on the pulley surface is causing the mounting
                    bolts to lose torque, allowing the pulley to come off.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If the repair has not been previously completed and before ordering parts, make
                            arrangements with the customer to have all applicable International&#174; MaxxForce DT, 9
                            and 10 engine AFC's completed during a single visit. Only order parts for vehicles that have
                            been scheduled with the customer.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Not every engine in the date range above is affected. This campaign is engine serial
                            number specific. Only perform this repair on units marked in ISIS.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
